body:
Minimal code example is attached. I encountered this while compiling a primitive library for an FPGA. A workaround is to comment out the primitives which use a dynamic delay ;)

causing_assertion_fail.v :

```
module causing_assertion_fail(i,o);
    input i;
    output o;

    time delay_in_always_statement;
    wire i,o;

    assign #(delay_in_always_statement,0) o=i;

    always @(i)
    begin
        delay_in_always_statement <= 0;
    end
endmodule
```

Compiler output (version 10.1) :

```
$ iverilog causing_assertion_fail.v
ivl: vvp_scope.c:753: draw_delay: Assertion `ivl_expr_type(fall_exp) == IVL_EX_SIGNAL' failed.
sh: line 1: 12861 Done                    /usr/lib/ivl/ivlpp -L -F"/tmp/ivrlg2714ca24f" -f"/tmp/ivrlg714ca24f" -p"/tmp/ivrli714ca24f"
